      <div xml:id="DayInWorld"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="death"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>           We had a grief</l>
               <l>we didn't understand while</l> 
               <l>           standing at the edge of</l>
               <l>   some low scrub hills as if</l>
               <l>humans were extra</l>
               <l>   or already gone;—</l>
               <l>                         </l>
               <l>what had been in us before?</l>
               <l>          a life that asks for mostly</l>
               <l>    wanting freedom to get things done</l>
               <l>in order to feel less</l>
               <l>          helpless about the end</l>
               <l>of things alone—;</l>
               <l>                          </l>
               <l>when i think of time on earth,</l>
               <l>   i feel the angle of gray minutes</l>
               <l>          entering the medium days</l>
               <l>    yet not "built-up":: our</l>
               <l>work together: groups, the willing</l>
               <l>    burden of an old belief,</l>
               <l>                           </l>
               <l>           and beyond them love, as of</l>
               <l>    a great life going like fast</l>
               <l>creatures peeling back marked</l>
               <l>    seeds, gold-brown integuments</l>
               <l>    the color time</l>
               <l>  will be when we are gone—</l>
        <l>           Brenda Hillman</l> 
               <note><ref target="#DayInWorld"></ref></note>
